other_tests.findings: Trace bilateral pleural effusions; gallstones in the gallbladder with mild gallbladder wall edema; mild acute interstitial pancreatitis indicated by slightly prominent pancreatic head and increased diffusion signal abnormality; no suspicious focal liver lesion; normal appearance of liver, kidneys, spleen, and adrenal glands; no intra or extrahepatic biliary dilatation; no evidence of stricture or obstruction in the bowel.
